  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Temp Staff (After School Engagement Programme)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Scope:</strong></p><ul><li>Design and implement activities in the school’s UPLIFT Room so as to provide High Needs Students (HNS) with a safe and conducive place to be in after school hours</li><li>During these activities, to also engage and build rapport with HNS so as to educate, equip, and empower them with pro-social skills and resilience.</li><li>Provide HNS with a positive adult figure that they can look to for support and in times of need (e.g., social-emotional support, positive role model).</li><li>Work closely with school staff to follow up on any concerns relating to the student (e.g., safety and well-being)</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong><br /></p><ul><li>Educational qualification certificates/transcripts, testimonials that are relevant in supporting HNS (e.g., counselling, trained to build socio-emotional skills)</li><li>Able to design and implement activities for the drop-in centre (please provide sample or programme outlines to demonstrate this)</li><li>Experience in working with and supporting HNS. Please provide examples such as place of employment in supporting HNS (e.g., track record of the contractor’s personnel)</li><li>Current company’s experience in providing related Manpower services (e.g., track record of the company)</li></ul><p><strong>Working Hours: </strong>Mondays, Tuesdays, Thursdays and Fridays: 1:30pm to 5:00pm</p><p>• Service not required on Saturdays, Sundays, gazetted public holidays and school holidays / school admin days</p><p><strong>Contract Period: </strong>23 Feb 2026 to 17 Nov 2026 (Option to extend from the period 1 Jan 2027 to 20 Nov 2027)</p><p><strong>Location:</strong> Woodlands</p><p>EA License No.: 96C4864</p><p>Reg No.: R26159658 BRANN LEONG CHUN HOE </p>",
